<p class="">I am speaking to the right hon. Gentleman who moved the Amendment. His colleague, the right hon. Member for Bournemouth (Mr. Bracken) is, I understand, going to address us tomorrow. The right hon. Member for Southport made no reference to Cable and Wireless. Therefore, I may be allowed to say a word about it. The new Board appointed by the Government is doing a very good job of work. Our public service is cheaper than the private service in the United States. One may send a message from New York for 1s. 3d. a word, and from London for 9d. a word.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
